@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<section class="hero-panel">
    <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="section-kicker">Accessible visual system</p>
        <h1>Bold color can still feel clean, focused, and easy to read.</h1>
        <p class="hero-lede">
            FireCharts now demonstrates an editorial-bright direction: warm neutrals, assertive accents,
            disciplined spacing, and interaction states that stay legible for keyboard and screen-reader users.
        </p>

        <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button-link button-link--primary" href="linechart">Explore line charts</a>
            <a class="button-link" href="barchart">View bar charts</a>
            <a class="button-link" href="piechart">View pie charts</a>
            <a class="button-link" href="weather">View data table</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-card" aria-label="Design pillars">
        <p class="hero-card__label">Three anchors</p>
        <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Readable contrast and visible focus styles</li>
            <li>Colorful surfaces without noisy backgrounds</li>
            <li>Charts that communicate through labels and states, not color alone</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="feature-grid" aria-label="System highlights">
    <article class="feature-card">
        <p class="feature-card__eyebrow">Typography</p>
        <h2>Crisp hierarchy</h2>
        <p>Headings do the expressive work while body copy stays calm and highly legible on soft surfaces.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="feature-card">
        <p class="feature-card__eyebrow">Color</p>
        <h2>Warm neutrals, bright accents</h2>
        <p>A restrained canvas lets orange, coral, and amber accents feel premium instead of overwhelming.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="feature-card">
        <p class="feature-card__eyebrow">Accessibility</p>
        <h2>Designed for clarity</h2>
        <p>Focus visibility, semantic structure, motion controls, and contrast all ship as part of the visual style.</p>
    </article>
</section>
